  "text": "PipeNet [CITATION_1] 12] , another low-latency design proposed around the same time as Onion Routing, gave stronger anonymity but allowed a single user to shut down the network by not sending. Systems like ISDN mixes [CITATION_2] were designed for other environments with different assumptions.",
